UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 479
1 AN ACT relating to undesignated glucagon.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 217 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 As used in Sections 1 to 4 of this Act:
6 (1) "Administer" means to directly give glucagon;
7 (2) "Authorized entity" means a public, private, or parochial school that has a
8 trained individual who is:
9 (a) Present on the premises or officially associated with the entity; and
10 (b) Trained as required under Section 2 of this Act to administer undesignated
11 glucagon;
12 (3) "Diabetes medical management plan" means a written, individualized diabetes
13 care plan prepared by the student's treating diabetes practitioner or practitioner
14 team that prescribes or directs how the student's diabetes needs may be met in the
15 school setting, including the administration of undesignated glucagon;
16 (4) "Pharmacist" has the same meaning as in KRS 315.010;
17 (5) "Practitioner" has the same meaning as in KRS 217.015;
18 (6) "Trained individual" means a school employee or contractor who has
19 successfully completed an approved education training program under KRS
20 158.838; and
21 (7) "Undesignated glucagon" means glucagon prescribed in the name of an
22 authorized entity in accordance with Sections 1 to 4 of this Act.
23 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 217 IS CREATED TO
24 READ AS FOLLOWS:
25 (1) A practitioner, acting within the practitioner's scope of practice, may prescribe
26 undesignated glucagon in the name of an authorized entity for use in accordance
27 with this section.
Page 1 of 4
