UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 479
1 individual who administers or provides undesignated glucagon if that individual
2 is acting as a Good Samaritan under KRS 313.035 and 411.148.
3 SECTION 3. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 217 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) Any authorized entity or trained individual that, in good faith and without
6 compensation, renders emergency care or treatment by the use of undesignated
7 glucagon under Sections 1 to 4 of this Act shall be immune from civil liability for
8 any personal injury resulting from the care or treatment, or resulting from any
9 act or failure to act in providing or arranging further medical treatment, if the
10 person acts as an ordinary, reasonably prudent person would have acted under
11 the same or similar circumstances.
12 (2) The immunity under subsection (1) of this section applies to:
13 (a) A practitioner who prescribes or authorizes the emergency use of
14 undesignated glucagon;
15 (b) A pharmacist who fills a prescription for undesignated glucagon;
16 (c) A trained individual who administers or provides undesignated glucagon;
17 (d) An authorized entity that acquires and stocks undesignated glucagon, or
18 provides undesignated glucagon to a trained individual; and
19 (e) An individual trainer or training entity providing the required training to a
20 trained individual.
21 (3) The immunity under subsection (1) of this section shall not apply if the personal
22 injury results from the gross negligence or willful or wanton misconduct of the
23 person rendering the care or treatment.
24 SECTION 4. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 217 IS CREATED TO
25 READ AS FOLLOWS:
26 The Cabinet for Health and Family Services, in consultation with the American
27 Diabetes Association, shall promulgate administrative regulations in accordance with
